cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.CE

The paper deals with the mapping of land use land cover using remote sensing data and machine learning techniques. The use of TerraSAR-X data and discriminative Markov random fields with spatio-temporal priors suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of import vector machines and the need to handle high spatial-temporal variability suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The study region being in Brazil and the mention of deforestation frontier suggests a focus on graphics (cs.GR) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
